OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FHousing child asylum       
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fseekers in hotels ruled    
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Funlawful                   
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The "routine" housing of unaccompanied 
OL,6, child asylum seekers in hotels is      
OL,7, unlawful, the High Court has ruled.    
OL,9,FThe charity Every Child Protected      
OL,10,FAgainst Trafficking (ECPAT) brought    
OL,11,Flegal action against the Home Office   
OL,12,Fover the practice.                     
OL,14,FThe High Court said children could be  
OL,15,Fplaced in hotels for "very short       
OL,16,Fperiods in true emergency situations"  
OL,17,Fbut not "systematically or routinely". 
OL,19,FThe Home Office said it had "no option"
OL,20,Fbut to temporarily use hotels.         
